value.0: The Watcher keeps an eye on those who enter the facility, ensuring that all who come do so with intent to use the offered services as intended. One cannot elude the Watcher. It indicates the presence of all, to ensure the safety of patrons and their goods.

Helms such as these have only recently begun to surface in the region, however they look ancient. Relics of an old war, long forgotten and a time nearly lost, these powerful artifacts were likely worn by the champions or paragons of the people that created them.

While the original creators of these helms seem to remain unknown, they do bare an uncanny resemblance to the natives of the Mylock Hills.

Loosely nailed, this wooden crate appears intended for temporary storage.
A sturdy crate, made from the type of black stone that is usually found in the areas of the Underdark that are inhabited by the drow.
The books lay piled atop each other with little in the way of rhyme or reason, as if someone was interrupted while in the process of returning them to their place.
Metal studs poke through the woodwork of this ornate chest. Judging by the fine craftsmanship, this strongbox appears to have been intended for public display.
Strange runes and pictographs, likely arcane in nature, have been scorched into the sides of this hide-covered strongbox.
